Commentary: back of a length on middle and leg, defends
Commentary_short: Paterson to Soumya Sarkar, no run

Commentary: offline and Sarkar punishes him for it, four to deep backward square leg. He has a good plan, bowl short and cramp the left-hander. But this one sits up for the pull shot
Commentary_short: Paterson to Soumya Sarkar, FOUR runs

Commentary: swing as he pitches the ball up, and it takes the ball wide down leg. De Kock throws himself to his right and gets a glove on the ball. Otherwise it would have been five wides. There is something definitely wrong with his right hand. He keeps looking at it, angrily
Commentary_short: Paterson to Soumya Sarkar, 2 wides

Commentary: up there for the drive and Kayes smashes it back at the bowler. Good on Paterson to take the pace off it
Commentary_short: Paterson to Imrul Kayes, 1 run

Commentary: slower ball outside off, Kayes tries to lash it over cover, but ends up with an outside edge to third man
Commentary_short: Hendricks to Imrul Kayes, 1 run

Commentary: excellent shot, behind square leg, a la Sanath Jayasuriya! Shuffles onto off stump and whips the ball off his hips with the greatest of ease
Commentary_short: Hendricks to Soumya Sarkar, FOUR runs

Commentary: even better, with the ball sailing over cover! Hendricks has let himself down bowling length and outside off and Sarkar only has to hit through the line
Commentary_short: Hendricks to Soumya Sarkar, FOUR runs

Commentary: takes the pace off - it's the ball off the back of the hand - and Sarkar pulls it to deep square leg
Commentary_short: Hendricks to Soumya Sarkar, 1 run

Commentary: he sends a full toss down the throat of deep square leg! The ball was there to be tossed into the junk pile outside the boundary. Especially considering there can be only two fielders out there now. And Kayes picks out one of them with a flick shot
Commentary_short: Hendricks to Imrul Kayes, OUT
Dismissal_text: Imrul Kayes c Miller b Hendricks 10 (16m 11b 1x4 0x6) SR: 90.90

Commentary: lots of heat on this short delivery, a shade outside off. Shakib tries to use that pace and bounce to his advantage, trying an upper cut. But he's too late on the shot
Commentary_short: Hendricks to Shakib Al Hasan, no run

Commentary: starts with a slower ball that somehow holds in the pitch and surprises Sarkar. Rears up at his chest and he does well to block it down the pitch
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Soumya Sarkar, no run

Commentary: back of a length on leg stump, clips it to midwicket
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Soumya Sarkar, no run

Commentary: tries to glide a back of a length delivery to third man, but he can't connect
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Soumya Sarkar, no run

Commentary: can't bowl short at his pace, can't bowl it down leg at his pace. Sarkar swivels on the back foot and finds the boundary behind square leg - and there is protection down there, all for naught
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Soumya Sarkar, FOUR runs

Commentary: gets down the track, but seeing that he doesn't have the room to have a free swing, he taps the shortish delivery down to mid-off
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Soumya Sarkar, 1 run

Commentary: mid-off is up and though Shakib doesn't time the ball, he is able to get enough to clear the infield. Bangladesh are keeping up with the required run-rate. But they're going to have to go at 10s for the entire innings.
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Shakib Al Hasan, FOUR runs

Commentary: huge appeal for lbw but that might have pitched outside leg. It's the slower ball to start, which is a very good idea on this pitch, especially when it is at a full length. Sarkar shapes to flick but he isn't able to pull it off
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Soumya Sarkar, no run

Commentary: full toss on middle, Sarkar has positioned himself beside it, and even then, he hits cover
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Soumya Sarkar, no run

Commentary: another missed opportunity, with a slower ball on leg stump, and Sarkar finds short fine leg. A little to either side and it would have been four
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Soumya Sarkar, 1 run

Commentary: wanders outside leg, which prompts Phehlukwayo to follow him with a slower ball. That's exactly what Shakib wants as he then shifts back in line with the stumps and sweeps to fine leg
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Shakib Al Hasan, 1 run

Commentary: full on middle and leg, Sarkar drives inside out to cover
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Soumya Sarkar, 1 run

Commentary: races down the track for a heave over long-on, but fresh air is all he meets
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Shakib Al Hasan, no run

Commentary: strikes him on the thigh! This one is at 134 kph, cramping Sarkar on off stump. The batsman tries to pull, but the ball sneaks under his bat, suggesting it isn't all that short
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Soumya Sarkar, no run

Commentary: 113 kph, on the pads, and a lot slower, Sarkar clips it to long leg
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Soumya Sarkar, 1 run

Commentary: places the swipe wide of long-on and finds the boundary. Shakib backs away, he gambles that the bowler is going to bowl short, he's ready for it and hoists the ball over the infield
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Shakib Al Hasan, FOUR runs

Commentary: length on leg stump, heaves it to deep midwicket. Shakib is picking his spots superbly. Last ball, mid-on was up. This ball, midwicket is up and South Africa pay for it
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Shakib Al Hasan, FOUR runs

Commentary: slower delivery on leg stump, Shakib backs away to slog it and misses altogether
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Shakib Al Hasan, no run

Commentary: he's skied it, it's going to be a tough catch, and AB's the man running back from mid-off and he takes it without any fuss whatsoever. Frylinck has his maiden T20I wicket, and he's worked it out with a slower ball. It's in line with the stumps and Shakib, eager to keep the boundaries going, lifts it over the off side. It was a good plan, considering the off side fence was less protected. But he can't get enough power in the shot and AB races across the turn, tracking the ball all the way, and snaffling it so very easily
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Shakib Al Hasan, OUT
Dismissal_text: Shakib Al Hasan c de Villiers b Frylinck 13 (14m 8b 3x4 0x6) SR: 162.50

Commentary: tosses it up on off stump, flicks it to long-on
Commentary_short: Duminy to Mushfiqur Rahim, 1 run

Commentary: gets down the pitch to clip a good length ball on middle through midwicket.
Commentary_short: Duminy to Soumya Sarkar, 2 runs

Commentary: stays back to a fuller delivery and tries to flick all around it. Inside edge saves him from an lbw
Commentary_short: Duminy to Soumya Sarkar, no run

Commentary: spears it in off a round-arm action, which slides down the leg side as Sarkar sweeps
Commentary_short: Duminy to Soumya Sarkar, 5 wides

Commentary: flicks the length ball neatly to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Duminy to Soumya Sarkar, 1 run

Commentary: tosses it up on off stump, Mushfiqur blitzes it to cover
Commentary_short: Duminy to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run

Commentary: slog sweeps it over the midwicket boundary. B-e-a-utiful hit. Spots the length ball so very early, gets across on off stump to open up the leg side and connects perfectly
Commentary_short: Duminy to Mushfiqur Rahim, SIX runs

Commentary: starts around the wicket to the left-hander, who sweeps the good length ball on leg stump to short fine leg
Commentary_short: Phangiso to Soumya Sarkar, no run

Commentary: fierce sweep, but there is a deep square leg in place for that shot
Commentary_short: Phangiso to Soumya Sarkar, 1 run

Commentary: tosses it up outside off, Mushfiqur lunges forward and flicks it to long-on
Commentary_short: Phangiso to Mushfiqur Rahim, 1 run

Commentary: in the hitting arc, and Sarkar swings it away to the midwicket boundary. Gets momentum into the shot by running down the track, taking it off a length and sending it soaring
Commentary_short: Phangiso to Soumya Sarkar, SIX runs

Commentary: flatter delivery on off stump, Sarkar flicks it through midwicket
Commentary_short: Phangiso to Soumya Sarkar, 1 run

Commentary: short third man and point are up, and Mushfiqur premeditates, and nails, a reverse sweep! If Phangiso had pitched this ball a few inches fuller, he wouldn't have been able to get under the ball. Such a risky shot.
Commentary_short: Phangiso to Mushfiqur Rahim, FOUR runs

Commentary: full and targeting middle, and it pins the advancing Sarkar on the pads while playing a flick across the line. Out comes a huge lbw appeal, but the umpire reckons its not out. South Africa discuss and they go up for the review. The question is about impact - is it in line - and whether the batsman is too far down the track. And DRS gives three reds! Umpire Holdstock has to reverse his decision and the local fans celebrate
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Soumya Sarkar, OUT
Dismissal_text: Soumya Sarkar lbw b Phehlukwayo 47 (44m 31b 5x4 2x6) SR: 151.61

Commentary: defends the shortish delivery on off stump to point
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Sabbir Rahman, no run

Commentary: goes short and targets Sabbir's body, but the ball slithers down leg
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Sabbir Rahman, 1 wide

Commentary: full on off stump, defends to mid-off, who is on the edge of the circle for a quick single
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Sabbir Rahman, 1 run

Commentary: tailing into the pads and Mushfiqur sends it flying to deep square leg
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Mushfiqur Rahim, 1 run

Commentary: comes down the track, but Andile spots int and sends down a quick and short delivery. Sabbir is wary of the scary piece of leather coming to his chest and awkwardly fends it to point
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Sabbir Rahman, no run

Commentary: another short ball - but it's off target, slipping down leg
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Sabbir Rahman, 1 wide

Commentary: drives to mid-off to keep the strike
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Sabbir Rahman, 1 run

Commentary: tapped to short cover first up, tossed up outside off, and defended
Commentary_short: Phangiso to Sabbir Rahman, no run

Commentary: worked off the hips towards midwicket, no one inside the circle in front of square and the bowler has to race across the green to retrieve that
Commentary_short: Phangiso to Sabbir Rahman, 1 run

Commentary: follows the batsman down the leg side, good length on middle and leg, and cramps Mushfiqur, can't whip the ball away
Commentary_short: Phangiso to Mushfiqur Rahim, no run

Commentary: Shouts of catch it, and taken by AB! Pitched up full on middle and the batsman can't resist the slog. Goes down on one knee but can't get the elevation. South Africa kept their best fielder at that spot, and the dividends have been rich
Commentary_short: Phangiso to Mushfiqur Rahim, OUT
Dismissal_text: Mushfiqur Rahim c de Villiers b Phangiso 13 (18m 8b 1x4 1x6) SR: 162.50

Commentary: uppishly hit over the bowler's head for a couple, dances down the pitch and tries to launch one, but takes the toe end of the bat. Falls safely ahead of long on and long off. Because the shot was mistimed, did he manage to get the two though
Commentary_short: Phangiso to Mahmudullah, 2 runs

Commentary: tucked square on the leg side off his hips, goes to the sweeper-fielder on the leg side
Commentary_short: Phangiso to Mahmudullah, 1 run

Commentary: pokes at it and goes past his outside edge, good length ball just outside off, tries to cut late but cannot make the desired contact
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Mahmudullah, no run

Commentary: In the air! And another one gone. Back of a length this time, and Mahmudullah looks to slog over the leg side. The bat turns, and takes the leading edge. Amla, near point, has to get under the ball, and manages to take the catch while running backwards. Settled himself right in time before tumbling
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Mahmudullah, OUT
Dismissal_text: Mahmudullah c Amla b Phehlukwayo 3 (4m 4b 0x4 0x6) SR: 75.00

Commentary: slow full toss on middle, punched down the ground for a single
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Sabbir Rahman, 1 run

Commentary: driven towards mid on for a single, can't make the connection he's looking for. Quick call for the run
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Mohammad Saifuddin, 1 run

Commentary: short on middle and leg, worked off his hips to deep midwicket. A great over from Phehlukwayo, but one ball to go
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Sabbir Rahman, 1 run

Commentary: full toss just outside off, manages to get this on the leg side, midwicket races in and ensures it stays down to one
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Mohammad Saifuddin, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length just outside off, tapped to long on with soft hands. The slowness allows for the extra run
Commentary_short: Phangiso to Mohammad Saifuddin, 2 runs

Commentary: worked in front of square on the leg side, the fielder at cow corner races in. But the big gaps on the leg side are allowing for easy singles
Commentary_short: Phangiso to Mohammad Saifuddin, 1 run

Commentary: Into the stands! Dances down the pitch and picks this delivery from outside off. Full swing of the bat, along with the arm's extension. Gets the distance. Straight over long off
Commentary_short: Phangiso to Sabbir Rahman, SIX runs

Commentary: That's AB, baby! He can't take the catch, but saves a certain six! Slogged towards the leg side, but De Villiers races to his left, and times his jump perfectly. AB doesn't risk it, he throws the ball back before going over the ropes. Saves some runs for certain. Will go down as dropped though
Commentary_short: Phangiso to Sabbir Rahman, 1 run

Commentary: goes down the leg side, good length on middle, but angling down
Commentary_short: Phangiso to Mohammad Saifuddin, 1 wide

Commentary: punched off the back foot towards cover
Commentary_short: Phangiso to Mohammad Saifuddin, 1 run

Commentary: tucked off the hips behind square for one
Commentary_short: Phangiso to Sabbir Rahman, 1 run

Commentary: dances down the wicket, and punched back to Hendricks
Commentary_short: Hendricks to Sabbir Rahman, no run

Commentary: overpitched outside off, almost near the batting crease and despite the batsman making some room, he can't squeeze it behind square. Goes through to de Kock
Commentary_short: Hendricks to Sabbir Rahman, no run

Commentary: Beautiful! Just lifted it over Hendricks' head, and the arm's extension takes it all the way. As straight as possible, and that goes just over the rope between the two fielders at long on and off. A good length ball that was converted into something slightly fuller by charging down
Commentary_short: Hendricks to Sabbir Rahman, SIX runs

Commentary: full outside off, cannot get the loose ball away, play-and-miss
Commentary_short: Hendricks to Sabbir Rahman, no run

Commentary: back of the hand this time, it's very short and no pace on that delivery. Sabbir is through his shot too early, and his bat turns upwards while trying to slog over extra. He manages to slice it, and mid off has no trouble swallowing that
Commentary_short: Hendricks to Sabbir Rahman, OUT
Dismissal_text: Sabbir Rahman c Phehlukwayo b Hendricks 19 (20m 16b 0x4 2x6) SR: 118.75

Commentary: very full just outside off, squeezed away to cover for a quick run
Commentary_short: Hendricks to Mehidy Hasan Miraz, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length outside off, opens the bat's face and punches square off the back foot. Goes past point's right and four crucial runs
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Mehidy Hasan Miraz, FOUR runs

Commentary: takes the pace off the ball, spongy bounce through to Mehidy, can only slice the ball towards Amla at point
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Mehidy Hasan Miraz, no run

Commentary: drops his hands and takes off for the single, full outside off
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Mehidy Hasan Miraz, 1 run

Commentary: tucked behind square for a single, full on leg stump, but can't play it as fine as he would've liked. Just to short fine leg's left
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Mohammad Saifuddin, 1 run

Commentary: muscled past point for a single, charged down the wicket but hit the high part of the bat, dribbles away towards deep extra
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Mehidy Hasan Miraz, 1 run

Commentary: slower ball to end the over, good length on leg stump and he fails to get any connection. Has to settle for leg byes
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Mohammad Saifuddin, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length outside off stump, waits for it and cuts from near his body to short third man. Smart bowling, the pace is off
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Mohammad Saifuddin, 1 run

Commentary: uses the width of the crease and angles it into the right hander, the batsman shuffles to the leg side but the bowler follows him, cramped for room and only manages to muscle the ball towards short midwicket
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Mehidy Hasan Miraz, 1 run

Commentary: gets the boundary, but probably not how he had it planned. Tried to slog the ball over extra  but the bat's angle takes it over short third man for four
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Mohammad Saifuddin, FOUR runs

Commentary: full just outside off, misses the big heave
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Mohammad Saifuddin, no run

Commentary: low full toss on off stump, Miller at cover gets a knock on his finger while trying to field that
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Mohammad Saifuddin, 1 run

Commentary: slow delivery, and equally short, but the batsman is up to the challenge. Wild slog towards the leg side, but goes straight over long on for six. Duminy almost considered going for the catch, but the ball sailed oh-so-slowly over his head. Useful runs
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Mehidy Hasan Miraz, SIX runs

Commentary: can't get this short-ish ball away, mistimed and Paterson races to his left after his followthrough to restrict
Commentary_short: Paterson to Mohammad Saifuddin, 1 run

Commentary: The leg stump is off! Tries to shuffle towards the off side to paddle the ball fine behind square, but can't get bat to ball and the delivery crashes onto the third pole. Went too far across, exposing all three wickets. 'You miss, I hit' stuff from Paterson
Commentary_short: Paterson to Mehidy Hasan Miraz, OUT
Dismissal_text: Mehidy Hasan Miraz  b Paterson 14 (12m 8b 1x4 1x6) SR: 175.00

Commentary: a beautiful yorker on middle stump, smacks him near his toe, a ripper to the new batsman and Paterson appeals. Not out, says the umpire, but they're going for the review. It was a peach first up, replays show it hit him boot-first in front of leg stump. This one's going to crash into middle stump. The umpire reverses his decision. Paterson on a hat-trick
Commentary_short: Paterson to Taskin Ahmed, OUT
Dismissal_text: Taskin Ahmed lbw b Paterson 0 (5m 1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0.00

Commentary: somehow dug away, almost a yorker on off stump, takes the leading edge and the ball goes towards the leg side instead
Commentary_short: Paterson to Shafiul Islam, 1 run

Commentary: slower one, worked around the corner to fine leg. Full on leg stump. Singles won't do it any more
Commentary_short: Paterson to Mohammad Saifuddin, 1 run

Commentary: good length just outside off, a big tail-ender slog from the batsman. Goes past his outside edge and through to QDK
Commentary_short: Paterson to Shafiul Islam, no run

Commentary: more slower deliveries, full just on off, cut square along the ground to the the fielder in the deep. That's Bangladesh's 150 but still 46 to go
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Mohammad Saifuddin, 1 run

Commentary: uppishly driven, and sliced over cover...well almost. Miller at cover races back and holds on to the ball that might have been swirling in the air. Makes the catch look easy
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Shafiul Islam, OUT
Dismissal_text: Shafiul Islam c Miller b Frylinck 1 (5m 3b 0x4 0x6) SR: 33.33

Commentary: Timed! Pulled in front of square, and just past the fielder at cow corner. Short on middle and that shot made the noise off the bat that would've made any top order batsman proud
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Mohammad Saifuddin, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on leg, goes just past leg stump as the batsman tries to make room to play it. Eventually the ball is too close to his body, and he can't make contact
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Mohammad Saifuddin, no run

Commentary: Well held by QDK! Full on leg and angling down the leg side. The keeper does really well to throw himself at the ball
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Mohammad Saifuddin, 1 wide

Commentary: slower ball, back of a length just outside off, all the batsman can do is tuck it to the sweeper in the deep on the leg side
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Mohammad Saifuddin, 1 run

Commentary: slower ball to end his maiden outing. Full on off stump, defended back to Frylinck
Commentary_short: Frylinck to Rubel Hossain, no run

Commentary: perfect yorker first up, right on leg stump, Saifuddin does extremely well to keep the ball away
Commentary_short: Paterson to Mohammad Saifuddin, no run

Commentary: backs away to the leg side to hoick this, the bowler follows him, pitching full outside leg, takes the inside edge and flies away to fine leg
Commentary_short: Paterson to Mohammad Saifuddin, 2 runs

Commentary: short outside leg stump, it's the offcutter, and it loops over the batsman's shoulder as he tries to cut it away behind point
Commentary_short: Paterson to Mohammad Saifuddin, no run

Commentary: yorker on leg stump, squeezed away to long on. Calls early for the double
Commentary_short: Paterson to Mohammad Saifuddin, 2 runs

Commentary: full toss on middle, bunted back to Paterson
Commentary_short: Paterson to Mohammad Saifuddin, no run

Commentary: short one to finish his spell, gets big onto the lower-order batsman. Does well to get his face out of the delivery's way
Commentary_short: Paterson to Mohammad Saifuddin, no run

Commentary: full on off, driven to cover and called early for the single, direct-hit from Miller at the non-striker's, but the batsman was home
Commentary_short: Hendricks to Rubel Hossain, 1 run

Commentary: my, my, a six! Pitched up on middle and leg, and Saif brings out the short-arm jab. Over cow corner for a six. Too little, too late. Or is it?
Commentary_short: Hendricks to Mohammad Saifuddin, SIX runs

Commentary: back of a length just outside edge, tries to pull over deep midwicket, but can't get the connection. Top edges, and falls just in short of the fielder in the deep
Commentary_short: Hendricks to Mohammad Saifuddin, 1 run

Commentary: short outside off, brings out the tennis-bat smash over the bowler's head and through to long on
Commentary_short: Hendricks to Rubel Hossain, 1 run

Commentary: short and wide outside off, cut square and the sweeper-fielder has it covered. Oh no, he doesn't. It's misfielded, the ball goes between his legs as he tries to field
Commentary_short: Hendricks to Mohammad Saifuddin, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on middle, punched to mid of for some runs and that's it! South Africa win by twenty runs.
Commentary_short: Hendricks to Mohammad Saifuddin, 2 runs
